Node Names from a Network Object

Source: R/internal-utils.R
get_nodes.Rd

Extracts the names of nodes (vertices) from a network object. This is for internal use for network types in the JaB package

Usage

get_nodes(network)

Arguments

network

A network object with \(n\) nodes. Network can be represented as a matrix, dgCMatrix edgelist, or igraph). See make_network_type for details.

Value

A vector of node names. If node names are not assigned, it returns a sequence of integers from 1 to \(n\).

See also

detect_type, make_network_type

Examples

data(paul.revere)
get_nodes(paul.revere)
